{
  "texts": [
    "GAT is a mechanism that operates within the models to focus on important interactions and features, contributing to accurate synergy score predictions.",
    "In Model Numcharoenpinij et al. (2022), GAT is employed in the GNN model based on the Message-Passing Neural Network (MPNN) framework.",
    "These weights guide the aggregation process, allowing the model to focus on critical interactions.",
    "In the Muthene (Yue et al. Page 23 of 38 49 2023), GAT creates meta-path-specific embeddings for end/central nodes by assigning weights to neighbor features based on attention mechanisms.",
    "In CGMS model (Wang et al. 2023), GAT is used within the Heterogeneous Graph Attention Network (HAN)."
  ]
}